  "body": "As you know, Solidity allows [passing functions](https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/types.html#function-types) (technically function pointers) as parameters:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity 0.8.20;\r\n\r\ncontract FunctionPointerTest{\r\n\r\n    function f1(function() external func) external {\r\n        func();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI was wondering how to pass this in Remix as an argument? For `external` functions, the \"function pointer\" is the encoded tuple `(address,selector)`.\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/assets/25297591/3ce19d66-220e-47a9-8534-65b6c05ef801)",
